The paper proposes a new model that combines convolutional neural networks with SMILES augmentation for molecular prediction. This work involves machine learning techniques and focuses on improving the accuracy of molecular prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves computer vision techniques (convolutional neural networks) and natural language processing techniques (SMILES augmentation), which suggest the sub-categories cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as likely options. Additionally, the paper involves the use of ensemble learning and regularization techniques, which suggest the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as possible options.
